ol.li: Google offers National Corporate Housing for interns in NYC, while providing spreadsheet for interns to find room openings and roommates.
For interns who found housing by themselves, it could be hard to determine where the shuttle bus stops were, as the locations were only provided by text before the internship started.
A visualized bus route map could be provided for prospective interns to better select housing options.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(77, 77, 77); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 487px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal;

li.span: The fact that each team have to submit a detailed proposal for internship headcounts resulted in clearly articulated internship goals, which were seen as very positive for interns.

ol.li: Mentors who allow interns to explore their interests while providing resourceful guidance and accessible means of communication are appreciated by interns.
Mentors and managers who cannot commit to timely instructions (responding within 3 hours) should be considered to be replaced or supplemented by a secondary role.
Google does great job documenting resources for interns to familiarize themselves with the project.
However, sometimes interns may still need mentor's guidance to interpret data and find relevant resources. When mentors are not around, interns may feel lost.
Interns may feel intimidated by the mentors at first, or tried to hide their feelings and questions. These feelings should be minimized.
Mentors should establish a communication system with the intern that entails who should be proactive asking what questions, and how.
Google offers a lot of activities for interns, some are intern-only, and some are company'wide events. Interviewees participated an avg. of 3 Google-held events throughout their internship period.

Tailor-made communities can be created for interns who represent smaller groups at Google intern. Suggestions include grad-only intern happy hours, UX intern online communities for all US interns at Google, etc.
